3.10	Kayavarohan	Kayavarohan	Kayavarohan is a village in the Vadodara district of the state of Gujarat, India. Kayavarohan is popularly known as Karvan and is situated on the National Highway 8 at a distance of 30 km from Vadodara. Kayavarohan is the birth place of Lakulish, the 2nd Century C.E. Shaivite revivalist, reformer and propounder of the pashupata doctrine. It is an important religious place on account of its Shiva temple in Lakulish avatar.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/India_Gujarat_location_map.svg/250px-India_Gujarat_location_map.svg.png
